As Asia wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/24/2004 at 03:44:20 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>The side of a rectangular prism have areas of 3cm², 6cm² and 8cm². 
>What is the volume of the prism?
>
>[Difficulty]
>I don't understand how to find out the volume of the prism.
>
>[Thoughts]
>I think to figure it out you do 3cm²x6cm²x8cm²

Hello Asia,

If the sides of the prism have lengths a, b, and c, then b*c=3, a*c=6, and a*b=8.  Solve 
this system.


